\sum_{k = 1}^n \frac1{k + 1}\binom{n}{k}
\binom{n}{k} \frac{n+1}{k+1} = \frac{n!}{k! (n-k)!} \frac{n+1}{k+1} = \frac{(n+1)!}{(k+1)! (n-k)!} = \binom{n+1}{k+1}
\sum_{k=0}^{n+1} \binom{n+1}{k} = 2^{n+1}
